A very short howto for this prototype:
---------------------------------------

Create a pad 100kb:
---------------------------------------
Create your pad:	
dd if=/dev/urandom of=Alice.entropy bs=100k count=1

Create the reversed pad:
./pad.py reverse Alice Bob

You have now a file called Alice.entropy and one called Bob.entropy. You keep the one called Bob.entropy and you send the one called Alice.entropy to Bob over a SECURE channel. You can delete the file Alice.entropy.


Encrypt the message "Hello World!":
---------------------------------------
Alice: 	./pad.py encrypt Bob

The encrypted message will look somehow like this: 33|7aYuzvnYCjVQXkaG


Decrypt the message:
---------------------------------------
Bob:	./pad.py decrypt Alice


Good luck!














